<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="average-n">average <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'ævərɪdʒ/    美 /'ævərɪdʒ/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>平均；平均数：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The average of 3, 8 and 10 is 7. 
数字3、8、10的平均数是7。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I spend <strong>an average of</strong> about $200 a year on books.
我平均每年大约花200美元买书。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>一般水平；平均标准：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>below / above</strong> <strong>average</strong>
低于/超过平均水平</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>the national average</strong>
全国平均水平</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="on-average">on average</h3>
<p>1.<strong>平均；一般地：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>On average we have five classes a day. 
我们平均每天上五节课。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Women, on average, live longer.
女性一般更长寿。</p><footer>2016 四川</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>He was a good student and scored<strong><em>_</em></strong>___ (高于平均水平) in most subjects.   （2011 天津改）  </li>
<li>Last year the number of students who graduated with a driving license reached 200,000, <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ average of 40,000 per year.   （2010 江西改）  </li>
<li>On <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (平均), people who don’t smoke are healthier than people who do.   （2009 全国）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. above average  2. an  3. average  </p></div>